Package com.inrupt.client

Application interfaces for the Inrupt client libraries.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Authenticator
    An interface for handling authentication challenges.
    Authenticator.Provider
    An authentication mechanism that knows how to authenticate network connections.
    Authenticator.Registry
    A registry for authentication mechanisms.
    Client  
    Client.Builder  
    Dataset
    A simple RDF dataset abstraction.
    Graph
    A simple RDF graph abstraction.
    Quad
    An RDF Quad.
    Request.BodyPublisher
    An API for serializing an HTTP Request.
    Response<T>
    An HTTP Response.
    Response.BodyHandler<T>
    An interface for mapping an HTTP response into a specific Java type.
    Response.ResponseInfo
    Initial response info supplied to a Response.BodyHandler before the body is processed.
    Triple
    An RDF Triple.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Authenticator.AccessToken
    A class containing information about an OAuth 2.0 access token.
    Authenticator.Challenge
    Part of the HTTP Challenge and Response authentication framework, this class represents a challenge object as represented in a WWW-Authenticate Response Header.
    Authenticator.DPoP
    An abstraction for working with OAuth 2.0 Demonstrating Proof-of-Possession at the Application Layer (DPoP).
    ClientProvider  
    Headers
    A read-only view of a collection of HTTP headers.
    RDFNode
    An RDF node.
    Request
    An HTTP Request.
    Request.BodyPublishers
    Built-in Request.BodyPublisher implementations.
    Request.Builder
    A Request builder.
    Response.BodyHandlers
    Convenience methods for creating common Response.BodyHandler objects.
    VerifiableCredential
    A data object for a Verifiable Credential.
    VerifiablePresentation
    A data object for a Verifiable Presentation.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Syntax
    The names of concrete RDF Syntaxes.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    InruptClientException
    A generic Inrupt runtime exception for use as a superclass.
